  "last_gate": {
    "recommendation": "PROCEED",
    "rationale": "All three significant flags from iteration 1 have been resolved with concrete, correct approaches: absolute-to-flow layout conversion for sortable compatibility, TrackLabelContent extraction to avoid duplicate sortable registrations, and correct identification of the active coordinate path (computeDropPosition via useDragCoordinator) with TIMELINE_START_LEFT as the single propagation point. Weighted score dropped from 6.0 to 0. No unresolved flags remain. The plan is ready for execution.",
    "signals_assessment": "Weighted score trajectory 6.0 \u2192 0 across two iterations. Plan delta 85.3% reflects substantial revision that directly addressed all three flagged concerns. Zero recurring critiques. Zero scope creep flags remaining (footer button concern was narrowed to overlay-style buttons matching existing patterns). Preflight clean. No debt overlap with escalated subsystems.",
    "warnings": [
      "Steps 4+5 must be implemented atomically as specified \u2014 partial application would create duplicate sortable IDs or an orphaned sidebar.",
      "Verify that CSS `position: sticky; left: 0` works correctly inside the specific overflow container structure (nested overflow parents can break sticky positioning).",
      "The absolute-to-flow conversion in Step 1 should be validated visually before proceeding to later steps, as it's the foundational change everything else depends on."
    ],
    "settled_decisions": [
      {
        "id": "DECISION-001",
        "decision": "Canvas rows convert from absolute positioning to normal document flow with fixed heights.",
        "rationale": "Required for dnd-kit verticalListSortingStrategy compatibility. Clips inside rows remain absolutely positioned, so internal layout is unaffected."
      },
      {
        "id": "DECISION-002",
        "decision": "TrackLabelContent is extracted as a non-sortable component; the SortableRow wrapper in TimelineCanvas owns the single useSortable call per track.",
        "rationale": "Prevents duplicate sortable registrations. The drag handle listeners are passed down as props to TrackLabelContent."
      },
      {
        "id": "DECISION-003",
        "decision": "TIMELINE_START_LEFT increases to LABEL_WIDTH (144px) as the single source of truth for coordinate propagation.",
        "rationale": "All coordinate consumers already reference this constant \u2014 no per-file fixups needed. The dead-code resolveDropTarget is ignored."
      },
      {
        "id": "DECISION-004",
        "decision": "Labels use CSS position: sticky; left: 0 for horizontal scroll anchoring inside the canvas scroll container.",
        "rationale": "Well-supported in modern browsers. Provides the desired UX of labels staying visible during horizontal scroll while sharing the vertical scroll container."
      },
      {
        "id": "DECISION-005",
        "decision": "+Video/+Audio buttons move to an overlay position (matching existing text-add button pattern), not a footer row system.",
        "rationale": "Avoids scope creep and conflict with the existing below-last-row drop zone for creating new tracks."
      }
    ],
